                  <li class="program-course">
            <a href="/study/2014-2015/courses/edem-220" class="program-course-title">
              EDEM 220 Contemporary Issues in Education (3 credits)              <!---->            </a>
            <div class="program-course-description">
              <div class="program-course-description-inner">
                <div id="node-23218" class=" clearfix">
  
  
  
  <div class="meta">
    <p>Offered by: Integrated Studies in Ed (<a href="/study/2014-2015/node/608">Faculty of Education</a>)</p>
      </div>

  <div class="content">
    <h3>Overview</h3>

    <p>
      Admin &amp; Policy Studies in Ed              : An introduction to contemporary issues in education in local, national and international contexts, including a critical perspective on educational issues by drawing on a variety of analytical frameworks.          </p>

    <p class="catalog-terms">
      Terms:              Fall 2014          </p>

    <p class="catalog-instructors">
      Instructors:                        Lisa Trimble (Fall)                  </p>

    
